## 1.1 Learn the Market

```
🟢 Easy · ⏱ Week 1 · 💰 ₹0 (just your time)
```

**What it is:** You spend 5-7 days visiting your city's scrap market, talking to dealers, observing how trades happen, learning which metals exist, what they cost, and who buys them. You buy nothing this week. You only learn.

**Why this step matters:** This week replaces years of textbook education. By touching copper, brass, aluminum, steel, and electronic scrap physically, you learn what no course teaches — how to identify quality by sight and weight, what the real street prices are (not Google prices), and who the actual players in your city are.

**How to do it:**

| Day | Action | What You Learn |
|---|---|---|
| Day 1 | Find your city's scrap market. Go there 9-11 AM. Walk every lane for 2 hours. | Market layout, what metals are traded, scale of operations |
| Day 2 | Talk to 5 copper/brass dealers. Ask "aaj copper ka rate kya hai?" | Live copper/brass prices, grading differences |
| Day 3 | Talk to 5 aluminum/steel dealers. Ask same questions. | Aluminum and steel grades, prices, who buys |
| Day 4 | Find the electronic scrap section. Talk to 3 e-waste dealers. | Circuit board prices, phone board prices, connector prices |
| Day 5 | Ask 3 dealers "aap kisko bechte ho?" Visit ONE of their buyers. | The selling chain — who buys from dealers and at what markup |
| Day 6 | Ask dealers "koi WhatsApp group hai trading ka?" Join 3-5 groups. | Live deal flow, real-time prices across cities |
| Day 7 | Write down ALL prices in a notebook. Compare with MCX prices online. | Price benchmarking, how street prices relate to exchange prices |

**Scrap market locations by city:**

| City | Main Scrap Market | Secondary Markets |
|---|---|---|
| Hyderabad | Afzalgunj, Falaknuma | Moazzam Jahi Market area, Jeedimetla industrial |
| Delhi | Mayapuri Phase 1 & 2 | Mundka, Seelampur (e-waste) |
| Mumbai | Dharavi | Kurla, Mankhurd |
| Bangalore | KR Market area | Peenya industrial, Yeshwanthpur |
| Chennai | Sowcarpet | Ambattur industrial, Perungudi |
| Pune | Bhavani Peth | Hadapsar, Pimpri-Chinchwad industrial |
| Kolkata | Tangra | Dhapa, Topsia |
| Ahmedabad | Rakhial | Naroda, Vatva industrial |

**Common mistake:** Being afraid to talk to scrap dealers because they look rough or the market looks dirty. Scrap dealers are the friendliest businesspeople in India. They love talking about their trade. They respect anyone who shows genuine interest. Walk in confidently. Say you want to learn this business. They will teach you for free.

**One-liner:** Week 1 is your free MBA — no classroom, no fee, just a scrap market and your curiosity.

**Checklist:**
```
✅ Located my city's scrap market
✅ Visited for at least 3 days
✅ Talked to 10+ dealers
✅ Noted prices for copper, aluminum, brass, steel, electronic scrap
✅ Joined 3+ WhatsApp trading groups
✅ Identified 3+ buyers (larger dealers or recyclers)
✅ Created price tracking notebook
```

