**What can go wrong:**

| Risk | Probability | Impact | How to Handle |
|---|---|---|---|
| Buy wrong grade at high price | High (first 3 trades) | Lose ₹1,000-3,000 | Always verify grade with experienced dealer before paying |
| Buyer offers less than expected | Medium | Lower profit by ₹500-1,000 | Get price confirmation on phone BEFORE transporting |
| Metal price drops while holding | Low (if you sell within 3 days) | Lose ₹500-2,000 | RULE: Never hold more than 3 days |
| Cheated on weight | Medium | Lose ₹500-2,000 per deal | ALWAYS weigh on YOUR scale at buying AND selling |

**Common mistake:** Trying to trade 5 different metals from day one. Start with ONLY copper for the first 5-10 trades. Become an expert in one metal's grades, prices, and buyers. Then add aluminum. Then brass. Depth beats breadth.

**One-liner:** Your first 5 trades will teach you more about commerce than 5 years of reading — ₹10,000 and courage is all you need.

