## 2.1 Get SPCB Authorization

```
🟡 Medium · ⏱ Month 8-10 · 💰 ₹5,000-15,000 (application fees)
```

**What it is:** State Pollution Control Board consent to operate as an authorized e-waste collector and dismantler. This is the single most important license in your entire journey. Without it, everything you do with e-waste is technically unauthorized. With it, you become one of a limited number of legal operators — and that limitation IS your competitive moat.

**Why this step matters:** Three reasons. First, SPCB authorization lets you provide disposal CERTIFICATES to companies — the certificate is your product, not the scrap. Second, electronics brands can only partner with SPCB-authorized collectors for EPR compliance. Third, unauthorized e-waste handling carries ₹5 lakh fine and imprisonment. Being authorized protects you AND excludes unauthorized competitors.

**How to apply — step by step:**

| Step | Action | Documents Needed | Time |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Apply online on state SPCB portal | Business registration (proprietorship/LLP/company) | Day 1 |
| 2 | Submit documents | PAN, Aadhaar, address proof, rent agreement for facility | Day 1-3 |
| 3 | Submit process description | What e-waste categories you handle, collection process, storage plan | Day 3-5 |
| 4 | Pay application fee | ₹5,000-15,000 (varies by state) | Day 5 |
| 5 | SPCB inspection | Inspector visits your facility/godown | Week 4-8 |
| 6 | Consent issued | Valid for 5 years, renewable | Week 8-12 |

**Timeline varies by state:**

| State | Typical Timeline | Difficulty |
|---|---|---|
| Maharashtra | 2-3 months | 🟡 Medium |
| Karnataka | 1-2 months | 🟢 Easy |
| Telangana | 2-4 months | 🟡 Medium |
| Tamil Nadu | 2-3 months | 🟡 Medium |
