# 10 Rules

| Rule | What It Means | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|
| 1. Never skip phases | Each phase builds skills and capital for the next | Jumping to Phase 3 without Phase 1-2 skills = failure |
| 2. Cashflow first, always | Don't invest in Phase N+1 until Phase N is profitable | Running out of cash kills more companies than bad ideas |
| 3. Regulatory compliance is your moat | Every license you get is a barrier competitors must also cross | SPCB authorization takes months — that delay protects you |
| 4. Environmental safety is non-negotiable | 20-30% of facility budget for ETP and safety | One spill = permanent shutdown + criminal prosecution |
| 5. Hire experts before you need them | Get metallurgist 6 months before chemical processing starts | Experts prevent mistakes that cost 100x their salary |
| 6. Patent everything | Every process improvement = file a patent | Process patents last 20 years and block competitors |
| 7. Government is your partner | Ministry of Mines, KABIL, CPCB want you to succeed | Engage proactively, attend consultations, apply for every scheme |
| 8. International relationships start early | Attend global mining conferences from Year 3 | The order in Year 10 comes from the handshake in Year 3 |
| 9. Document everything from Day 1 | Weight, purity, waste, training — all recorded | Investors, regulators, and customers audit documentation |
| 10. Phase 1 is not the empire — it's the launchpad | Don't fall in love with scrap trading | Use it to earn, learn, and fund the next phase |

